Fort LeBoeuf Middle School added a new photo.
January 17 at 2:16 PM ·

During the January 16, 2020, School Board meeting, Tish Bartlett and Heather Evans from the Autism Society of Northwestern PA presented a banner to members of the Bison Strong Committee to recognize the Fort LeBoeuf School District as the 2019 Walk for Autism winner for the most funds raised by a school. The FLB SD raised over $6300 for the Autism Society of NWPA with almost 200 walkers representing our District and our community! Pictured: Jaimie Travis, FLB High School Autistic Support Teacher Garrett Bartlett, FLB High School Student Nancy Maloney, FLB Elementary Autistic Support Teacher Tish Bartlett, Executive Director of the Autism Society of NWPA Heather Evans, FLB Parent and Chair Family for the 18th Annual Walk for Autism Logan Evans, Waterford Elementary School Student Erin Strimel, FLB Middle School Autistic Support Teacher Yvonne Best-Proctor, Waterford Elementary School Principal Kristi Rathburn, FLB SD Director of Student Support Services #bisonpride #oneherd #leavealegacy #servingothers — view on Instagram https://ift.tt/38fvh9K

“We wanted to provide an update to our families. Our district administration met with Pennsylvania State Police this morning. They are currently investigating the source of the social media post from last night. Anyone who might have information related to the post is encouraged to contact the PSP at 898-1641 or report via our internal tip line or the Safe2Say tip line. In terms of the decision to open our district schools tomorrow, we will continue to evaluate the status of the investigation and contact families with an update later today. Again we apologize for the inconvenience caused by this situation as we work to ensure the safety and security of our students and staff.” Sincerely, Rick Emerick — view on Instagram https://ift.tt/2IlqngT
